## BLACKHORSE PROTOCOL — CROSS-REFERENCE MAP

The Blackhorse Protocol repo lives at ../blackhorse/ relative to this project.
When making ANY cryptographic or encoding decision in Sentinel, check here first.

### Protocol File References

  ../blackhorse/__init__.py
    → Package entry. __version__ = "0.1.0", all 7 stages complete.

  ../blackhorse/core/__init__.py
    → Stage 1: BitStream, RingBuffer, utils
    → Use RingBuffer for any sliding-window buffer needs in Sentinel

  ../blackhorse/language/__init__.py
    → Stage 2: BHLEncoder, BHLDecoder, BHLPacket
    → BHL_MAGIC = b'BHL\x1A'
    → When Stage 6 of Sentinel begins: wrap artifact hashes in BHLEncoder before signing

  ../blackhorse/compression/__init__.py
    → Stage 3: Compressor, Decompressor — AVAILABLE

  ../blackhorse/crypto/symmetric/__init__.py
    → Stage 4: ChaCha20Cipher — AVAILABLE (256-bit key, 96-bit nonce)

  ../blackhorse/crypto/asymmetric/__init__.py
    → Stage 5: Curve25519, KeyPair — AVAILABLE (X25519 ECDH + HKDF-SHA256)

  ../blackhorse/crypto/signing/__init__.py
    → Stage 6: BHLSigner, SignedPacket — AVAILABLE (HMAC-SHA256)

  ../blackhorse/interface/__init__.py
    → Stage 7: BlackhorseSession — AVAILABLE (full pipeline)

  ../blackhorse/docs/BHL_SPEC.md
    → Full Blackhorse Language specification
    → The authoritative reference for all BHL encoding decisions

  ../blackhorse/tests/
    → 144 passing tests covering all 7 Protocol stages

### Protocol Stage → Sentinel Stage Dependencies

  Protocol Stage 1 (core/)        → Available. Use for binary utilities if needed.
  Protocol Stage 2 (language/)    → Available. BHL encoding ready.
  Protocol Stage 3 (compression/) → Available. Use for report compression.
  Protocol Stage 4 (crypto/sym/)  → Available. ChaCha20 ready.
  Protocol Stage 5 (crypto/asym/) → Available. Curve25519 ready.
  Protocol Stage 6 (crypto/sign/) → Available. HMAC-BHL signing ready.
  Protocol Stage 7 (interface/)   → Available. Full pipeline ready.

  Rule: For crypto decisions in Sentinel Stage 6+, delegate to the Protocol.
  Never re-implement cryptographic primitives independently.

