## PRODUCT OVERVIEW

Blackhorse Sentinel is a verification infrastructure platform that allows
organizations to ingest artifacts (PDFs, URLs, text, images, structured data),
hash + timestamp them with ISO 8601 + SHA-256, link evidence to structured
assertions, and export versioned Technical Verification Reports with integrity proofs.

### The 4-Step Core Flow
1. Ingest Artifacts    → Upload PDFs, URLs, text, images, or structured data sources
2. Hash + Timestamp    → Each artifact receives SHA-256 hash and ISO 8601 timestamp
3. Link Evidence       → Connect assertions to supporting artifacts with structured verification
4. Export Report       → Generate versioned Verification Report with integrity proofs

---

## TECH STACK

Primary: TypeScript + Next.js 14 (App Router)
Styling: Tailwind CSS
Database: SQLite / better-sqlite3 (Stage 1) → PostgreSQL / Supabase (Stage 4)
Storage: Local (Stage 1) → S3-compatible Cloudflare R2 (Stage 4)
Hashing: SHA-256 + SHA-3-512 (node:crypto, server-side only)
Timestamps: ISO 8601, UTC, server-assigned
Auth: TODO Stage 4 (Clerk or Auth.js)
API: REST (Stage 1) + tRPC (Stage 2+)
PDF Generation: React PDF or Puppeteer (Stage 3)
Deployment: Vercel or Cloudflare Pages
Testing: Vitest

Post-Quantum (Sentinel Stage 6+):
  → BHL encoding of hash records    — via ../blackhorse/language/__init__.py
  → HMAC-SHA256 signing             — via ../blackhorse/crypto/signing/__init__.py
  → Curve25519 key exchange         — via ../blackhorse/crypto/asymmetric/__init__.py
  → ChaCha20 encryption             — via ../blackhorse/crypto/symmetric/__init__.py
  → Full pipeline                   — via ../blackhorse/interface/__init__.py
  → Do NOT re-implement these. Use the Protocol directly.

