## AI ASSISTANT RULES (for Cursor AI)

1.  Never skip tests. Every function gets a test.
2.  Never use `any`. Create a proper type instead.
3.  Never store plaintext sensitive data. Hash first, always.
4.  When in doubt about security, choose the more conservative option and note it.
5.  Never build ahead of CURRENT STAGE without explicit owner instruction.
6.  Comments explain WHY, not WHAT. The code explains what.
7.  Every API endpoint: input validation + auth check (Stage 4) + typed response.
8.  For ALL crypto decisions: check ../blackhorse/docs/BHL_SPEC.md first.
9.  For Protocol feature availability: all 7 stages are built and tested.
10. This product changes lives. Treat every line with that weight.
11. If you see a conflict between Sentinel code and Protocol spec — the Protocol wins.
12. Never re-implement post-quantum crypto. Use the Protocol (all stages available).

